                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Mediocre and irregular.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; vermilion.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Wäldä Muse</persName>Wäldä Muse is mentioned as the scribe in the supplication formula, fol. 17r, l.9. However, the handwriting appears to be dissimilar from that of the scribe Wäldä Muse attested in some other manuscripts (e.g., SMM-004, UM-023, MR-016 etc.); but it appear similar to Ms. SMM-006.<date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>none</item>
                        </list>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The broadly spaced handwriting is characterized by thin and tall letters, slightly slanted to the right. <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
- The loops of ግ and ቆ are in many cases very pronounced. <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
- The top of some letters is sometimes extends beyond the headline: cp. ቶ on fols. 2v l.9, 14r l.1; ት on fol. 7v l.1; ግ e.g., fols. 8v, l.8, 9v, l.1 fol. 19v l.5.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">
- The vowel marker of ይ has a hook shape, particularly rounded and curved (e.g., fols. 2v l.10, 3r, ls. 4 and 9). <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic">
- The word እግዚአብሔር is usually written with ligature (ግ and ዚ, e.g., fols. 2v l.8, 7v l.3).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
